When an `async` function throws synchronously, the runtime automatically rejects its returned Promise. The caller's `try/catch` around `await parseData(...)` (etc.) catches it just as it would catch an explicit `return Promise.reject(...)`, so wrapping the map in a second `try/catch` inside the helper would be redundant.

